Description: Rim and body sherd of South Ionian pottery cup; interior: reserved band at rim, glazed black below; exterior reserved save for black bands at rim and centre of sherd; also trace of black at bottom break.
Curator's comments: The cup is of 'Panionion' type or 'Ionian band-cup, with lightly offset lip, Schlotzhauer type 6.6.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.863)
